Re: Made up conversation in the present tense
by Yudan Taiteki » Tue 08.04.2009 10:09 pm Mr.Paper wrote:Um, first of all, desu is a verb.desu is usually not called a verb for Japanese because it doesn't operate like other words such as "wakaru" or "iku". It only operates as a copula after nouns (and na adjectives), after -i adjectives it only marks politeness and has no meaning.
-Chris Kern
Yudan Taiteki
